Racer - A drag racing practice tree 
Copyright 2012 Dave Hayes <dwhayes@gmail.com>
https://github.com/daveisadork/Racer


Usage: Racer.py [options]

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -t TYPE, --tree=TYPE  Sets tree type <pro400|pro500|sportsman>
                        [default: pro400]
  -r SECS, --auto-reset=SECS
                        Sets auto reset time in seconds (0 to disable).
                        [default: 0]
  -0, --zero-perfect    Shows a perfect reaction time as 0.000
  -f, --fullscreen      Enables fullscreen mode.
  -w WxH, --window-size=WxH
                        Sets the windowed resolution (ignored if fullscreen)
                        [default: 480x700]
  --left-lane=PLAYER    Sets left lane player type <computer|human>
                        [default: computer]
  --right-lane=PLAYER   Sets right lane player type <computer|human>
                        [default: human]
  --left-rollout=SECS   Sets left lane rollout time in seconds.
                        [default: 0.22]
  --right-rollout=SECS  Sets right lane rollout time in seconds.
                        [default: 0.22]
  --autostart-min=SECS  Sets the minimum delay for autostart in seconds.
                        [default: 1.0]
  --autostart-max=SECS  Sets the maximum delay for autostart in seconds.
                        [default: 3.0]
  --computer-reaction-min=SECS
                        Sets minimum computer reaction time in seconds.
                        [default: -0.009]
  --computer-reaction-max=SECS
                        Sets maximum computer reaction time in seconds.
                        [default: 0.115]
  -b, --double-buffering
                        Enables double buffering.
  -a, --hardware-accel  Enables hardware acceleration (fullscreen only).
  -s, --stats           Shows statistics for the current session.
  -d, --debug           Shows debugging output.

